title: Meissner and Oskar are called in.
on-arrival: hindenburg_hitler_r += 1

The President summons his chief of staff Meissner and his son Oskar to join the discussion. Meissner backs Papen’s proposal that [+ nsdap_chancellor +] be appointed Chancellor, with Papen serving as Vice Chancellor. He argues that this arrangement is the only viable path out of the political deadlock—and the best way to tame the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span>, pointing to the considerable number of cabinet posts [+ nsdap_leader +] has agreed to hand over to conservatives.

By the meeting’s end, however, both Hindenburg and his son remain unconvinced. They continue to press for Papen’s own return to the chancellorship instead.